------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
            Team Fortress 2 Disclaimer Version 1 (Added July 15th, 2017)

   Team Fortress 2 Vintage is a fork of the open source fan project, Team Fortress 2 Classic.
   
   Team Fortress 2 Classic is a reimagining of Team Fortress 2 created by the community 
   and is unrelated or attempting to be a copy, bootleg or ripoff of Team Fortress 2 and is a seperate 
   entity from Team Fortress 2.
   
   Team Fortress 2 Vintage is a stock/tournament based reimagining of older variants of Team Fortress 2 
   created by the community
   and is unrelated or attempting to be a copy, bootleg or ripoff of Team Fortress 2 and is a seperate 
   entity from Team Fortress 2 and Team Fortress 2 Classic.
   
   This mod was forked freely from TF2C by the open source license and the Source SDK license 
   and also distributes on the same open source license as per license requirements.
   Using this license anyone is free to branch, copy and fork TF2V with their own code as long 
   as the same licensing is applied to their project.
   
   This mod has no monetization or tries to monetize any portion of Team Fortress 2, 
   Team Fortress 2 Classic or any part of Team Fortress 2 Vintage. 
   No gifts have been given or received as a result of the creation of this mod.

   Team Fortress 2 Vintage is a free modification for the Source 2013 Multiplayer tools and will 
   always be free with no monetization opportunities as per the License agreement.
   
   This mod is intended to be played using the Source SDK Base 2013 Multiplayer tools on Steam and 
   only versions of the mod on Steam are supported.
   
   No standalone version of this mod bypassing Steam has been created or endorsed by any of 
   the official Team Fortress 2 Vintage team.
   
   No support is given for non-Steam versions of Team Fortress 2 Vintage, as these versions 
   violate the Source SDK License
   that TF2V is distributed under as well as violating the Steam EULA. In addition these 
   versions may also have viruses, trojans and keyloggers attached to them damaging your computer.
   
   USING NON-SUPPORTED VERSIONS OF TEAM FORTRESS 2 VINTAGE ARE AT YOUR OWN RISK. 
   ONLY DOWNLOAD AND PLAY OFFICIALLY RELEASED VERSIONS OF TEAM FORTRESS 2 VINTAGE.
   
   In order to securely enjoy Team Fortress 2 Vintage, Please use only official mirrors of 
   Team Fortress 2 Vintage and the most recent versions of Source SDK 2013 Multiplayer tools 
   found on Steam.
   
   Stay safe, and have fun.
